<title>USA: Benguet Corp Q4 shr loss widens.</title>
<headline>Benguet Corp Q4 shr loss widens.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-03-31</dateline>
<text>
<p>1996			1995</p>
<p> Shr loss		  $0.025     loss	$0.001</p>
<p> Net loss		   2,811   profit	   111</p>
<p> Revs			23,189		   26,173</p>
<p>			12 MONTHS</p>
<p> Shr loss		  $0.055   profit	$0.013</p>
<p> Net loss		   6,281   profit	 1,533</p>
<p> Revs			97,456		  111,452</p>
<p> Avg shrs		 114,111		  114,059</p>
<p>(All data above 000s except per share numbers)</p>
<p>NOTE: Benguet is based in the Philippines. Under Philippine generally accepted accounting principles, unrealized foreign exchange losses are deferred and amortized to coincide with the actual repayment of outstanding foreign currency obligation, while pension costs are actuarily computed and are funded as accrued.</p>
<p>The effect is to increase the firm's net loss by $923,000 in Q4 1996, and by $973,000 for full-year 1996. In 1995 the effect is to increase Q4 net income by $495,000, and to increase net income by $853,000 for the year.</p>
</text>
